Description: Egypt, view of Sphinx and pyramids in desert at El Gîza. Small groups of adult males standing in foreground, most wearing robes and head-gear. Three Europeans riding camels, wearing sailors' uniforms. Medium: Gelatin silver print.
Producer name: Photographed by: John Frederick Clifford Hunt
Curator's comments: Geography: El Gîza suggested by J M Hudson, 27/01/1998. Circumstances: The Imperial War Museum holds photographs from the same collection with a more military content - see [HUN-] PIC DOC 66.
